    <item>
      <title>Does one have to be a genius to do maths?</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 14 May 2007 01:01:11 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths&#34;&gt;Does one have to be a genius to do maths?&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Better beware of notions like genius and inspiration; they are a sort of magic wand and should be used sparingly by anybody who wants to see things clearly.&#xA;(José Ortega y Gasset, &amp;ldquo;Notes on the novel&amp;rdquo;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Does one have to be a genius to do mathematics?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Solving mathematical problems</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/solving-mathematical-problems/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 14 May 2007 00:44:38 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/solving-mathematical-problems/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/solving-mathematical-problems.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/solving-mathematical-problems/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/solving-mathematical-problems/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/solving-mathematical-problems/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;solving-mathematical-problems&#34;&gt;Solving mathematical problems&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Chaque vérité que je trouvois étant une règle qui me servoit après à en trouver d&amp;rsquo;autres [Each truth that I discovered became a rule which then served to discover other truths].&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;— René Descartes, &amp;ldquo;Discours de la Méthode&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Problem solving, from homework problems to unsolved problems, is certainly an important aspect of mathematics, though definitely &lt;strong&gt;not the only one&lt;/strong&gt;. Later in your research career, you will find that problems are mainly solved by knowledge (of &lt;strong&gt;your own field&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;of other fields&lt;/strong&gt;), experience, &lt;strong&gt;patience&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;hard work&lt;/strong&gt;; but for the type of problems one sees in school, college or in mathematics competitions one needs a slightly different set of problem solving skills. I do have a &lt;a href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/books/&#34;&gt;book on how to solve mathematical problems&lt;/a&gt; at this level; in particular, the &lt;strong&gt;first chapter&lt;/strong&gt; discusses general problem-solving strategies. There are of course several other problem-solving books, such as Polya&amp;rsquo;s classic &amp;ldquo;How to solve it&amp;rdquo;, which I myself learnt from while competing at the Mathematics Olympiads.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Work hard</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/work-hard/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 18:52:08 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/work-hard/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/work-hard.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/work-hard/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/work-hard/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/work-hard/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;work-hard&#34;&gt;Work hard&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Every mathematician worthy of the name has experienced … the state of lucid exaltation in which one thought succeeds another as if miraculously… this feeling may last for hours at a time, even for days. Once you have experienced it, you are eager to repeat it but unable to do it at will, unless perhaps by dogged work…&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;a href=&#34;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andr%C3%A9_Weil&#34;&gt;André Weil&lt;/a&gt;, “The Apprenticeship of a Mathematician”)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How to Work Hard</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/paul_graham/essays_en/hwh/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/paul_graham/essays_en/hwh/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/paul_graham/essays_zh/hwh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://www.paulgraham.com/hwh.html&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://www.paulgraham.com/hwh.html&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://www.paulgraham.com/hwh.html&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;how-to-work-hard&#34;&gt;How to Work Hard&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;June 2021&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It might not seem there&amp;rsquo;s much to learn about how to work hard. Anyone who&amp;rsquo;s been to school knows what it entails, even if they chose not to do it. There are 12 year olds who work amazingly hard. And yet when I ask if I know more about working hard now than when I was in school, the answer is definitely yes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
